cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG. 

The paper presents a computer vision method for identifying the boundary of materials in transparent vessels, which involves image processing and graph-cut algorithm. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves graphics and image processing, which makes cs.GR (Graphics) another likely category. The paper also involves machine learning and optimization, which makes cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval, as it deals with identifying properties of materials, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category.
